cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper describes a method for morphological annotation of written Korean text using language resources that can be easily updated. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of resources and the ability to control the evolution of the system suggests that machine learning techniques may be involved, which could also place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of accurate linguistic information, which could involve techniques from cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The system could also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE) due to its focus on language processing.
